definition.value: From DeltaMass: Average Mass: 16 Average Mass Change:16 Notes:Green et al. in J. B. C. 270, 18209-18211 (1995) quote Kim and Raines in Eur. J. Biochem. 224, 109-114 (1994). Kim and Raines using ESI-MS and sulfhydryl group titration found that bovine seminal ribonuclease contains a single oxidized sulfhydryl group, which cannot participate in a disulfide bond. This form of cysteine is called sulfenic acid (-SOH).
